<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-11-08T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-11-08T12:00:00-05:00" n="119" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d119">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">462.00 R 294/285: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Herrick</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-11-08T17:00:00+00:00"><hi rend="italic">November 8,
                                        1923—5 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received November 8—4:45
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>451. The Conference of Ambassadors this morning without any discussion
                            decided to communicate to the Reparations Commission the text of the
                            agreement relative to the costs of the American army of occupation. The
                            formula adopted was the one proposed by this Embassy.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Herrick</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>